going to The Tombs.

252
00:13:59.072 --> 00:14:00.307
All right?

253
00:14:00.373 --> 00:14:01.693
- You know your way out.
- Thanks.

254
00:14:04.611 --> 00:14:05.645
So then...

255
00:14:05.712 --> 00:14:07.480
I handed Dr. Bulba
the buy money.

256
00:14:07.547 --> 00:14:10.483
and he gave me a duffel
bag full of OxyContin.

257
00:14:10.550 --> 00:14:13.753
Great. Just like that
on the stand tomorrow.

258
00:14:13.820 --> 00:14:16.723
Dr. Lars Bulba.
aka "The Dentist."

259
00:14:16.789 --> 00:14:20.327
Biggest trafficker in illegal
prescription drugs in the tri-state area.

260
00:14:20.393 --> 00:14:23.196
I still can't believe a children's
dentist was selling drugs.

261
00:14:23.263 --> 00:14:26.399
He was pulling in over half
a million dollars a month.

262
00:14:26.466 --> 00:14:27.567
We're due in court at 9:00.

263
00:14:27.634 --> 00:14:29.536
I'll put Beaumont
on the stand first.

264
00:14:29.602 --> 00:14:31.138
Is the buy money secure?

265
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:33.516
It's in the evidence room. sealed
with the original paperwork.

266
00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:35.842
Okay. Get some rest tonight.

267
00:14:35.909 --> 00:14:39.179
If we land this case. I could
make Assistant District Attorney.

268
00:14:42.315 --> 00:14:44.355
It's not that big of a deal.
It happens to everyone.

269
00:14:44.417 --> 00:14:46.553
It doesn't happen to you.

270
00:14:46.619 --> 00:14:48.588
- True.
- How can it not bother you.

271
00:14:48.655 --> 00:14:51.191
being on the stand and knowing
that if you say the wrong thing.

272
00:14:51.258 --> 00:14:52.892
this guy could walk?

273
00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:55.762
All right. look.
Here's what I do.

274
00:14:55.828 --> 00:14:58.898
When I talk to a jury. I just
think about something I love doing.

275
00:14:58.966 --> 00:15:01.368
that makes me happy. When
you're happy. you're likeable.

276
00:15:01.434 --> 00:15:03.736
- Huh.
- So. what do you love doing?

277
00:15:04.904 --> 00:15:06.439
- And there we have it.
- Hey.

278
00:15:06.506 --> 00:15:08.308
That. uh. bomb-threat
trace came back in.

279
00:15:08.375 --> 00:15:10.453
Looks like it came from a cell
phone somewhere in the neighborhood.

280
00:15:10.477 --> 00:15:11.754
We're just trying
to narrow it down.

281
00:15:11.778 --> 00:15:12.956
Okay. Probably just
a prank call. huh?

282
00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:15.015
Hey. how you doing? I'm
looking for your CO.

283
00:15:15.082 --> 00:15:17.550
That'd be Alvarez. Alvarez!

284
00:15:17.617 --> 00:15:19.919
Detective. US
Marshal Gary Klunket.

285
00:15:19.987 --> 00:15:22.755
Well. it's US Marshal
night tonight.

286
00:15:22.822 --> 00:15:24.824
Pardon me?

287
00:15:24.891 --> 00:15:27.194
You have a Bo Keebler in
custody. is that correct?

288
00:15:27.260 --> 00:15:28.962
Well. we. uh...

289
00:15:29.029 --> 00:15:31.164
Do you or don't you. Detective?

290
00:15:31.231 --> 00:15:34.434
We did. Marshall Foster
signed him out 10 minutes ago.

291
00:15:34.501 --> 00:15:37.404
- Ben Foster?
- Yeah. little guy. hangdog. Why?

292
00:15:37.470 --> 00:15:38.905
Foster was suspended last week

293
00:15:38.972 --> 00:15:41.074
on suspicion of taking bribes.

294
00:15:41.141 --> 00:15:44.311
There's no way he's legally
escorting prisoners anywhere.

295
00:15:44.377 --> 00:15:46.813
But I ran his paperwork.
Everything checked out.

296
00:15:46.879 --> 00:15:50.283
It doesn't matter. You just gave
my prisoner to a suspected felon.

297
00:16:05.865 --> 00:16:08.835
Repeat after me. "My job
as a police detective

298
00:16:08.901 --> 00:16:11.704
"is to put criminals in jail.
not help them break out!"

299
00:16:11.771 --> 00:16:13.816
Maybe you want to write it
on the blackboard 100 times?

300
00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:15.475
It's not too late.
I can fix this.

301
00:16:15.542 --> 00:16:17.510
- How long have they been gone. Eddie?
- Half-hour.

302
00:16:17.577 --> 00:16:19.422
All right. Casey. why don't
you put out a finest message

303
00:16:19.446 --> 00:16:21.224
and see what we get back? They
couldn't have gone too far.

304
00:16:21.248 --> 00:16:23.316
I ran all of his paperwork.
Everything cleared.

305
00:16:23.383 --> 00:16:25.752
I don't get it. Eddie.
You are the rule king.

306
00:16:25.818 --> 00:16:27.630
Why would you let Keebler
go in the first place?

307
00:16:27.654 --> 00:16:29.522
It's...

308
00:16:29.589 --> 00:16:31.124
-You know what? Never mind.
-Right.

309
00:16:31.191 --> 00:16:32.792
Now I'm really curious.

310
00:16:32.859 --> 00:16:35.228
Well. I had Chicago send
over the original case file.

311
00:16:35.295 --> 00:16:37.597
Foster has nothing to do
with the Keebler case.

312
00:16:37.664 --> 00:16:39.232
- He lied to me.
- Really?

313
00:16:39.299 --> 00:16:41.268
He's a con man.
You got played.

314
00:16:41.334 --> 00:16:44.271
What I don't get is. what
does a dirty US Marshal want

315
00:16:44.337 --> 00:16:45.905
with the world's
dumbest convict?

316
00:16:45.972 --> 00:16:47.407
Excuse me.

317
00:16:47.474 --> 00:16:48.675
Shraeger.

318
00:16:48.741 --> 00:16:50.543
Sergeant Brown is gonna kill me.

319
00:16:50.610 --> 00:16:53.280
Eddie. you got to man up.

320
00:16:53.346 --> 00:16:56.983
We got 11 hours till the Sarge
gets back. We can fix this.

321
00:16:57.050 --> 00:16:58.518
Now. this is what you wanted.

322
00:16:58.585 --> 00:17:00.787
You're the boss. Take control.

323
00:17:02.422 --> 00:17:03.590
Yeah. thank you.

324
00:17:03.656 --> 00:17:06.025
Guys. that
was the tech unit.

325
00:17:06.093 --> 00:17:07.736
They finished the trace
on that bomb threat.

326
00:17:07.760 --> 00:17:09.862
Turns out it came from
inside the precinct.

327
00:17:09.929 --> 00:17:11.164
What?

328
00:17:11.231 --> 00:17:13.032
-Yeah.
-Terrific. So let's see.

329
00:17:13.100 --> 00:17:15.468
Keebler robs a
restaurant full of cops.

330
00:17:15.535 --> 00:17:18.071
gets arrested. Foster comes
in and breaks him out.

331
00:17:18.138 --> 00:17:20.316
And in between all of this.
someone calls in a bomb threat

332
00:17:20.340 --> 00:17:22.175
and clears out the
building for 30 minutes.

333
00:17:22.242 --> 00:17:23.410
Oh. this isn't happening.

334
00:17:23.476 --> 00:17:25.412
Maybe Keebler's not
the dumbest perp alive.

335
00:17:25.478 --> 00:17:26.989
Maybe he robbed that
Chinese restaurant

336
00:17:27.013 --> 00:17:28.291
because he wanted to get caught.

337
00:17:28.315 --> 00:17:30.650
Why would anyone
want to get arrested?

338
00:17:30.717 --> 00:17:33.920
I don't know. But I know a
way to find out. Come on.

339
00:17:52.705 --> 00:17:53.973
911. What's
your emergency?

340
00:17:54.040 --> 00:17:56.443
Hey. this is Detective
412 from the 2nd Precinct.

341
00:17:56.509 --> 00:18:00.513
I need a patrol car sent over to
622 Mulberry. apartment. uh...

342
00:18:01.281 --> 00:18:02.515
Uh...

343
00:18:02.582 --> 00:18:04.851
Third floor. above
the entryway door.

344
00:18:04.917 --> 00:18:06.519
Yes. possible assault.

345
00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:08.821
Victim is female.
Perp is male.

346
00:18:19.499 --> 00:18:23.236
This is the interview tape of Keebler
and Foster before the bomb threat.

347
00:18:23.303 --> 00:18:24.704
Here you go.

348
00:18:29.909 --> 00:18:31.444
Unhandcuff me. Hurry up!

349
00:18:31.511 --> 00:18:32.612
Son of a bitch.

350
00:18:32.679 --> 00:18:34.347
Is everything where
M said it was?

351
00:18:34.414 --> 00:18:36.483
Yeah. I saw the door
when they printed me.

352
00:18:36.549 --> 00:18:39.219
Go left out the room. one floor
down. third door on the left.

353
00:18:39.286 --> 00:18:41.588
It should be right
near the back.

354
00:18:41.654 --> 00:18:42.998
What are you doing?
They'll trace that.

355
00:18:43.022 --> 00:18:44.291
It's a throwaway.

356
00:18:44.357 --> 00:18:45.792
They'll never find us in time.

357
00:18:45.858 --> 00:18:47.170
Did you have a
problem with the CO?

358
00:18:47.194 --> 00:18:48.528
Are you kidding?

359
00:18:48.595 --> 00:18:50.005
That
guy was a total loser.

360
00:18:50.029 --> 00:18:53.533
I saw how to play
him from a mile away.

361
00:18:53.600 --> 00:18:57.170
Do not hang up. I planted
a bomb in the 2nd Precinct.

362
00:18:57.237 --> 00:19:00.006
and you have 15
minutes until it blows.

363
00:19:01.841 --> 00:19:04.377
Now. you remember exactly what
you're supposed to do. right?

364
00:19:04.444 --> 00:19:06.646
We give it at least a minute.

365
00:19:06.713 --> 00:19:08.581
Son of a bitch.

366
00:19:08.648 --> 00:19:10.983
So why'd they call
the bomb threat?

367
00:19:11.050 --> 00:19:12.485
They didn't need it to escape.

368
00:19:12.552 --> 00:19:14.287
Well. the bomb threat
cleared the building.

369
00:19:14.354 --> 00:19:16.223
They had 10 minutes
alone in the precinct

370
00:19:16.289 --> 00:19:18.558
before the bomb
squad got here. so...

371
00:19:18.625 --> 00:19:21.761
So why did two felons want to
be alone in a police precinct?

372
00:19:23.095 --> 00:19:24.335
It's the
evidence room.

373
00:19:25.532 --> 00:19:26.966
Officer Trunk. report.

374
00:19:27.033 --> 00:19:28.368
I just started inventory.

375
00:19:28.435 --> 00:19:30.903
So far. everything checks out.

376
00:19:30.970 --> 00:19:32.781
All right. look for
anything out of place. guys.

377
00:19:32.805 --> 00:19:34.974
Keebler said it was
somewhere in the back.

378
00:19:42.014 --> 00:19:43.350
Guys. I got an
empty evidence box.

379
00:19:44.784 --> 00:19:48.588
Space number 790.

380
00:19:48.655 --> 00:19:52.359
It's Cole and Beaumont's case.
That's $50.000 missing from this box.

381
00:19:52.425 --> 00:19:54.327
That's the case Nicole's
prosecuting tomorrow.

382
00:19:54.394 --> 00:19:56.429
This wasn't a breakout.
It was a heist.

383
00:19:56.496 --> 00:19:57.797
Oh. no.

384
00:20:14.247 --> 00:20:15.682
What's going on?

385
00:20:15.748 --> 00:20:18.951
- We got robbed.
- What?

386
00:20:19.018 --> 00:20:21.654
How can we get robbed?
We're a police station.

387
00:20:21.721 --> 00:20:24.724
Yeah. remember the genius that tried
to take the Chinese restaurant?

388
00:20:24.791 --> 00:20:27.026
Well. a dirty US Marshal
came in to pick him up.

389
00:20:27.093 --> 00:20:28.637
They're the ones that
called in the bomb threat.

390
00:20:28.661 --> 00:20:31.230
When the precinct was empty.
they raided the evidence room.

391
00:20:31.298 --> 00:20:33.266
Stole $50.000 from
the Dentist case.

392
00:20:33.333 --> 00:20:36.269
- What?
- There's no case without that money.

393
00:20:36.336 --> 00:20:38.204
It's my fault.

394
00:20:38.271 --> 00:20:39.739
I let the Marshal take him.

395
00:20:39.806 --> 00:20:41.508
Well. we have to tell Nicole.

396
00:20:41.574 --> 00:20:43.976
No. no. Not yet.

397
00:20:44.043 --> 00:20:46.513
I say we catch these guys.
get the money back tonight.

398
00:20:46.579 --> 00:20:48.548
Doesn't matter. Once they
break the evidence seal.

399
00:20:48.615 --> 00:20:50.550
the chain of custody
goes out the window.

400
00:20:50.617 --> 00:20:52.785
Well. then. we catch them
before they break the seal.

401
00:20:52.852 --> 00:20:54.253
- How?
- Yeah. How?

402
00:20:54.321 --> 00:20:55.688
The dentist.

403
00:20:55.755 --> 00:20:57.300
You think the dentist hired
them to tank the case?

404
00:20:57.324 --> 00:20:59.001
Well. there's plenty of
money in that evidence room.

405
00:20:59.025 --> 00:21:00.627
Why only take the one envelope?

406
00:21:00.693 --> 00:21:02.405
Well. the dentist has been
in jail since his arrest.

407
00:21:02.429 --> 00:21:05.298
which means there's got to be a
record if he contacted these guys.

408
00:21:05.365 --> 00:21:06.999
Phone calls. visitor log.

409
00:21:07.066 --> 00:21:08.868
Okay. let's pull
it. Pull it quietly.

410
00:21:08.935 --> 00:21:10.803
The minute this gets
out. we're done.

411
00:21:10.870 --> 00:21:13.005
- All right? Let's move.
- Walsh.

412
00:21:14.474 --> 00:21:15.875
Thank you.

413
00:21:15.942 --> 00:21:18.311
You need to call the US
Marshal's office. okay. Eddie?

414
00:21:18.378 --> 00:21:20.647
Just fill them in. but
tell them to keep it quiet.

415
00:21:20.713 --> 00:21:21.824
Threaten them if you have to.

416
00:21:21.848 --> 00:21:23.182
All we need is nine hours.

417
00:21:23.249 --> 00:21:25.318
If we don't get the
money back by then.

418
00:21:25.385 --> 00:21:26.919
it won't matter.

419
00:21:26.986 --> 00:21:28.788
You should be in charge.
you know. not me.

420
00:21:28.855 --> 00:21:30.890
Everybody has a
first day. Eddie.

421
00:21:30.957 --> 00:21:32.825
All that matters is
what you do next.

422
00:21:46.806 --> 00:21:48.475
Police! Open up!

423
00:21:52.111 --> 00:21:53.846
Are you kidding me?

424
00:21:55.648 --> 00:21:56.983
You call in about the assault?

425
00:21:57.049 --> 00:21:59.151
Yeah. yeah. yeah. across
the street. Is she okay?

426
00:21:59.218 --> 00:22:00.753
Yeah. we knocked.
No one answered.

427
00:22:00.820 --> 00:22:03.423
Super said he saw that tenant
go out earlier in the evening.

428
00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:05.057
No. No. no. no. I saw...

429
00:22:05.124 --> 00:22:07.860
Oh. let me guess.
You're a bird watcher.

430
00:22:07.927 --> 00:22:10.730
- That's not...
- Look. the girl was alone.

431
00:22:10.797 --> 00:22:13.132
- doing yoga.
- Yoga! That must've been great.

432
00:22:13.199 --> 00:22:15.001
Yeah. and the next
time I looked...

433
00:22:15.067 --> 00:22:16.845
Hey. you know it's against
the law to spy on people?

434
00:22:16.869 --> 00:22:19.271
Listen. fellas. I'm on the job.

435
00:22:19.338 --> 00:22:21.541
Detective Leo
Banks. 2nd Precinct.

436
00:22:21.608 --> 00:22:24.911
Oh! Then the girl
was. what. a suspect?

437
00:22:24.977 --> 00:22:26.045
Listen to me.

438
00:22:26.112 --> 00:22:27.747
You need to get
inside the apartment

439
00:22:27.814 --> 00:22:29.582
and see if there's any
signs of a struggle.

440
00:22:29.649 --> 00:22:31.618
You hear that. Gus?

441
00:22:31.684 --> 00:22:33.796
The detective here thinks we
need to get inside the apartment.

442
00:22:33.820 --> 00:22:36.298
Thank God he's here. Otherwise I
might forget how to wipe my butt.

443
00:22:36.322 --> 00:22:38.290
Very funny. Now. are
you gonna go over there.

444
00:22:38.357 --> 00:22:41.093
or do I need to call
the Squad Sergeant?

445
00:22:41.160 --> 00:22:43.162
What's with the
inflatable furniture?

446
00:22:43.229 --> 00:22:45.732
Get out. Thank you.
fellas. I'm done.

447
00:22:45.798 --> 00:22:47.810
Glad to be of service. sir.
You have a nice evening.

448
00:22:47.834 --> 00:22:50.036
Yeah. yeah. thanks. Wait.
What's her name? The yoga girl.

449
00:22:50.102 --> 00:22:53.239
This is a
professional request.

450
00:22:53.305 --> 00:22:54.541
- Carmen.
- Carmen what?

451
00:22:54.607 --> 00:22:56.075
- Carmen Dunn.
- Thank you.

452
00:22:56.142 --> 00:22:57.577
You have a nice day.

453
00:23:37.116 --> 00:23:39.251
J17-SBK...

454
00:23:39.318 --> 00:23:42.522
J17-SBK1.

455
00:23:47.460 --> 00:23:50.329
2120 hours. The suspects
leave the evidence room.

456
00:23:50.396 --> 00:23:52.899
That must be the dentist's
money in that green bag.

457
00:23:52.965 --> 00:23:55.134
So they hit a blind
spot for four minutes.

458
00:23:55.201 --> 00:23:57.003
Then they reappear here.

459
00:23:57.069 --> 00:23:59.739
and they enter the personal
effects holding area.

460
00:23:59.806 --> 00:24:02.909
It's the backpack. They put the
money in Keebler's backpack.

461
00:24:02.975 --> 00:24:05.545
which I returned to him.

462
00:24:05.612 --> 00:24:09.649
The dentist's prison log shows six calls
in two weeks to a pay phone on Avenue A.

463
00:24:09.716 --> 00:24:12.218
And I did a background check
on US Marshal Ben Foster.

464
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:15.454
Turns out he grew up on the same
street as the dentist in New Rochelle.

465
00:24:15.522 --> 00:24:17.199
They've been
friends since grade school.

466
00:24:17.223 --> 00:24:19.225
Great. so. that connects them.

467
00:24:19.291 --> 00:24:20.402
but that doesn't
help us find them.

468
00:24:20.426 --> 00:24:22.028
There you are!

469
00:24:22.094 --> 00:24:24.463
Oh. hey. honey.
We're just. uh...

470
00:24:24.531 --> 00:24:25.998
I thought you got
off at midnight.

471
00:24:26.065 --> 00:24:29.636
Uh. they stayed to help us out
with a case we're working on.

472
00:24:29.702 --> 00:24:32.972
Well. I need them rested
for trial in the morning.

473
00:24:33.039 --> 00:24:35.141
Eddie. can't you send them home?

474
00:24:35.207 --> 00:24:36.308
Uh...

475
00:24:38.477 --> 00:24:39.779
- Eddie?
- Uh. yeah.

476
00:24:39.846 --> 00:24:41.247
Uh. Beaumont. Cole.

477
00:24:41.313 --> 00:24:42.658
why don't you guys go
ahead and clock out?

478
00:24:42.682 --> 00:24:45.351
But we... We really want
to help on that case.

479
00:24:45.417 --> 00:24:46.853
Yeah. I know.

480
00:24:46.919 --> 00:24:48.120
Just go on home.

481
00:24:48.721 --> 00:24:49.789
Thanks. babe.

482
00:24:51.624 --> 00:24:53.192
You've
gotta be kidding me.

483
00:24:53.259 --> 00:24:56.395
I'm heading home myself.
get a few hours of sleep.

484
00:24:56.462 --> 00:24:57.664
Okay.

485
00:24:59.198 --> 00:25:01.233
- You okay?
- Uh. yeah. I'm fine.

486
00:25:01.300 --> 00:25:02.511
Yeah. Just go...
Get some sleep.

487
00:25:02.535 --> 00:25:05.204
- All right. Bye.
- Okay. Bye.

488
00:25:05.271 --> 00:25:09.542
I keep thinking about
something Foster said.

489
00:25:09.609 --> 00:25:12.845
He asked Keebler if everything
was "where M said it was."

490
00:25:12.912 --> 00:25:14.146
Who's... Who is "M"?

491
00:25:14.213 --> 00:25:16.583
Maybe an inside man? A cop?

492
00:25:16.649 --> 00:25:18.918
Oh. tell me it's not
another crooked cop.

493
00:25:18.985 --> 00:25:21.353
I could run new background
checks on support staff.

494
00:25:21.420 --> 00:25:23.455
What if it's not one
of us. but one of them?

495
00:25:23.522 --> 00:25:26.258
- "Them"?
- Yeah. two types of people in a police station.

496
00:25:26.325 --> 00:25:27.760
- Cops and criminals.
- Criminals.

497
00:25:27.827 --> 00:25:30.396
Yeah. We get the same perps
in and out of here every week.

498
00:25:30.462 --> 00:25:32.131
They know the place
as well as we do.

499
00:25:32.198 --> 00:25:35.301
So. we're looking for a
recidivist with the initial "M."

500
00:25:39.305 --> 00:25:41.540
- What?
- Marvin.

501
00:25:45.277 --> 00:25:48.615
Before you say anything. I
bought him with my own money.

502
00:25:48.681 --> 00:25:50.116
I even kept the receipt.

503
00:25:50.182 --> 00:25:51.651
This isn't about
the dummy. Marvin.

504
00:25:51.718 --> 00:25:55.154
Because I thought about what
you said. and you're right.

505
00:25:55.221 --> 00:25:56.422
I need a new gig.

506
00:25:56.488 --> 00:25:58.157
Get my act together.

507
00:25:58.224 --> 00:26:00.860
So. meet Marvin II.

508
00:26:00.927 --> 00:26:02.161
I'll say this much.

509
00:26:02.228 --> 00:26:04.764
I've never quite seen a
ventriloquist like you before.

510
00:26:04.831 --> 00:26:08.334
What's
that supposed to mean. biotch?

511
00:26:08.400 --> 00:26:09.836
Marvin. I'm serious.

512
00:26:09.902 --> 00:26:11.838
- Marvin!
- If that dummy says another word...

513
00:26:11.904 --> 00:26:14.206
Yeah? What are you gonna do?

514
00:26:14.273 --> 00:26:16.142
Uh... Uh... Cry?

515
00:26:17.977 --> 00:26:19.345
Hey!

516
00:26:19.411 --> 00:26:21.513
Marvin. has anyone approached
you in the last month

517
00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:23.916
regarding information about
the precinct's layout?

518
00:26:23.983 --> 00:26:25.618
- I'm okay.
- Marvin!

519
00:26:27.153 --> 00:26:28.888
Look at the photos.

520
00:26:30.923 --> 00:26:33.860
Hey. I know them! They
bought me drinks at the Ear.

521
00:26:33.926 --> 00:26:36.863
Uh. Bo and Ben. They
were really nice.

522
00:26:36.929 --> 00:26:38.530
That's right. What
did you tell them?

523
00:26:38.597 --> 00:26:42.034
I don't know. They just wanted
to know where some stuff was.

524
00:26:42.101 --> 00:26:45.037
Said they heard I was
"The Man" at the 2nd.

525
00:26:45.104 --> 00:26:46.839
"The Man." I like that.

526
00:26:46.906 --> 00:26:48.574
Oh. Marvin.

527
00:26:48.641 --> 00:26:49.742
What?

528
00:26:51.711 --> 00:26:54.847
- Oh. no. Did I screw up again?
- Mmm-hmm.

529
00:26:54.914 --> 00:26:57.416
These guys bluffed their
way into the precinct

530
00:26:57.483 --> 00:26:59.385
and stole $50.000 in evidence.

531
00:26:59.451 --> 00:27:01.921
It wasn't weird to you that they
were asking those questions?

532
00:27:01.988 --> 00:27:03.923
About a police station?

533
00:27:03.990 --> 00:27:06.893
They were nice. People
don't talk to me much.

534
00:27:08.127 --> 00:27:11.030
That's why I got
Marvin. He's my friend.

535
00:27:11.097 --> 00:27:14.166
You're killing me.
Marvin. You're killing me.

536
00:27:14.233 --> 00:27:17.804
Please tell me that you
remember something. anything.

537
00:27:17.870 --> 00:27:19.438
that's going to help
us with this case.

538
00:27:19.505 --> 00:27:22.041
I don't know. I
was pretty drunk.

539
00:27:22.108 --> 00:27:23.575
But there was a girl with them.

540
00:27:23.642 --> 00:27:26.278
Nancy? Nora?

541
00:27:26.345 --> 00:27:28.514
We went to a bar
near her apartment.

542
00:27:28.580 --> 00:27:30.649
-Where?
-You got me. It was in Brooklyn.

543
00:27:31.317 --> 00:27:32.852
But... Wait!

544
00:27:32.919 --> 00:27:34.887
There was a cow outside.

545
00:27:38.024 --> 00:27:40.126
- A cow.
- Definitely a cow.

546
00:27:40.192 --> 00:27:41.593
So she
lives in a field.

547
00:27:41.660 --> 00:27:43.629
No. An apartment.

548
00:27:45.064 --> 00:27:48.200
Marvin. You know where I have
to take you now. don't you?

549
00:27:48.267 --> 00:27:49.601
The Tombs.

550
00:27:49.668 --> 00:27:51.637
That's right.
Bring number two.

551
00:27:56.375 --> 00:27:57.476
Come on!

552
00:28:05.251 --> 00:28:07.186
-Delahoy.
-Hey. it's me. Don't hang up.

553
00:28:07.253 --> 00:28:09.488
I saw a man come out of the
building across the street.

554
00:28:09.555 --> 00:28:12.424
and I'm pretty sure he was
dragging a body in a duffel bag.

555
00:28:12.491 --> 00:28:14.827
- You saw the body?
- No. But it was a big duffel bag.

556
00:28:14.894 --> 00:28:16.495
- I'm hanging up.
- No. no! Wait!

557
00:28:16.562 --> 00:28:18.206
I got his license plate
number. My Internet's down.

558
00:28:18.230 --> 00:28:20.466
and I just need you
to run the plate.

559
00:28:20.532 --> 00:28:21.667
- That's it?
- That's it.

560
00:28:21.734 --> 00:28:23.803
Just run the plate. see
if he's got any priors.

561
00:28:23.870 --> 00:28:26.672
It's J17-SBK1.

562
00:28:26.739 --> 00:28:28.784
Maybe you could see if he has
any connection to Yoga Girl.

563
00:28:28.808 --> 00:28:30.542
Her real name's
Carmen Dunn. Two N's.

564
00:28:30.609 --> 00:28:32.087
Thought you said run
the plate and that's it.

565
00:28:32.111 --> 00:28:34.613
Eric. please. I think
something really...

566
00:28:36.148 --> 00:28:37.283
Really what?

567
00:28:37.884 --> 00:28:39.651
Dude. you there?

568
00:28:52.264 --> 00:28:54.333
He's back.

569
00:28:54.400 --> 00:28:56.335
He's in the apartment.

570
00:28:56.402 --> 00:28:57.770
Who's back?

571
00:29:00.439 --> 00:29:01.573
Leo?

572
00:29:02.274 --> 00:29:03.976
Hey. Leo.

573
00:29:04.643 --> 00:29:06.245
Fine. screw it.

574
00:30:26.926 --> 00:30:29.395
I'm not here. Leave a message.

575
00:30:29.461 --> 00:30:31.663
Hey. man. it's me.
You there? Pick up.

576
00:30:32.899 --> 00:30:34.533
Okay. look. I ran that
plate you gave me.

577
00:30:34.600 --> 00:30:37.069
The owner's name
is Reginald Worthy.

578
00:30:37.136 --> 00:30:39.906
He's been questioned in the
disappearance of one woman in Queens

579
00:30:39.972 --> 00:30:42.108
and another one in Rhode Island.

580
00:30:42.174 --> 00:30:45.177
He works at a photo lab in
the same mall as Yoga Girl.

581
00:30:45.244 --> 00:30:48.147
Uh. listen. man.

582
00:30:48.214 --> 00:30:50.682
I think this guy could
be a serial killer.

583
00:30:50.749 --> 00:30:53.485
Be careful. I'm on my way.

584
00:30:57.823 --> 00:31:00.002
Hey. babe.
Hey. babe. is something wrong?

585
00:31:00.026 --> 00:31:02.628
Sorry. I didn't mean to
wake you up. I just. um...

586
00:31:02.694 --> 00:31:04.230
I'm having a...

587
00:31:05.731 --> 00:31:08.334
I'm just having a tough night.

588
00:31:08.400 --> 00:31:10.536
Oh. honey. It'll be okay.

589
00:31:10.602 --> 00:31:12.104
Can we talk about
it after the trial?

590
00:31:12.171 --> 00:31:14.140
Oh. yeah.

591
00:31:14.206 --> 00:31:16.384
You're right. It's
late. you should get some sleep.

592
00:31:16.408 --> 00:31:17.852
You have... You have
a big day tomorrow.

593
00:31:17.876 --> 00:31:20.479
-Okay. I love you.
-I love you. too. Good night.

594
00:31:23.215 --> 00:31:24.350
Hi.

595
00:31:24.416 --> 00:31:25.417
Hi.

596
00:31:27.519 --> 00:31:29.588
You know that your. um...

597
00:31:29.655 --> 00:31:31.757
Your wife and I went to
high school together?

598
00:31:31.823 --> 00:31:33.225
- No. I didn't.
- Yeah.

599
00:31:33.292 --> 00:31:35.394
- We didn't really get along.
- Oh.

600
00:31:35.461 --> 00:31:37.329
I
actually hated her.

601
00:31:37.396 --> 00:31:38.564
A lot.

602
00:31:41.467 --> 00:31:44.803
But now I think she's.
you know. kind of cool.

603
00:31:45.704 --> 00:31:47.606
She's become her own person.

604
00:31:47.673 --> 00:31:51.143
I met Nicole when I was
still on foot patrol.

605
00:31:51.210 --> 00:31:53.412
She was in law school.

606
00:31:53.479 --> 00:31:55.347
I think she liked
that I carried a gun.

607
00:31:56.582 --> 00:31:57.749
And the mustache.

608
00:31:57.816 --> 00:31:59.618
- Of course.
- Yeah.

609
00:31:59.685 --> 00:32:01.820
For sure. Uh...

610
00:32:01.887 --> 00:32:03.398
But. you know. I knew
it was just a fling.

611
00:32:03.422 --> 00:32:04.856
There's no way a girl like that

612
00:32:04.923 --> 00:32:07.659
likes a beat cop
named Ed Alvarez.

613
00:32:07.726 --> 00:32:09.028
"Eddie" Alvarez.

614
00:32:09.095 --> 00:32:12.198
No. It was just "Ed" then.

615
00:32:12.264 --> 00:32:14.666
- Mmm.
- Just a gangly yutz from Mamaroneck

616
00:32:14.733 --> 00:32:17.569
who took his stepfather's last
name when he joined the force.

617
00:32:17.636 --> 00:32:20.139
so he could get promoted faster.

618
00:32:20.206 --> 00:32:22.108
Well. look what happened.

619
00:32:23.976 --> 00:32:26.412
She married you.

620
00:32:26.478 --> 00:32:29.881
You know. if it was up to me. I would
just be a detective. I would solve crimes.

621
00:32:29.948 --> 00:32:31.917
But Nicole...

622
00:32:31.984 --> 00:32:34.186
She deserves a
champion. you know?

623
00:32:34.253 --> 00:32:36.488
Not some guy with a cheap suit

624
00:32:36.555 --> 00:32:38.324
who punches the clock every day.

625
00:32:38.390 --> 00:32:41.227
That's what a
champion is. Eddie.

626
00:32:41.293 --> 00:32:42.561
Someone who'll do the work

627
00:32:42.628 --> 00:32:44.896
that other people
think is beneath them.

628
00:32:52.338 --> 00:32:54.640
Do you know where I can
find a cow in Brooklyn?

629
00:32:54.706 --> 00:32:57.009
- A cow?
- Yeah. Marvin said our suspects

630
00:32:57.076 --> 00:32:59.311
are staying at a place
with a cow outside.

631
00:32:59.378 --> 00:33:01.947
Oh. there's a cow in front
of Vaca's Steak House.

632
00:33:02.014 --> 00:33:05.484
But it's not a real
cow. It's a sculpture.

633
00:33:07.086 --> 00:33:08.854
You're a genius.

634
00:33:08.920 --> 00:33:10.489
- What?
- What do you say. boss?

635
00:33:10.556 --> 00:33:11.923
Want to go catch some bad guys?

636
00:33:11.990 --> 00:33:13.259
Hell. yes.

637
00:33:26.405 --> 00:33:28.074
Police! Don't move.

638
00:33:29.408 --> 00:33:30.876
Drop the bag.

639
00:33:32.644 --> 00:33:33.712
Put your hands up.

640
00:33:35.581 --> 00:33:36.715
Who's the joke now. bitch?

641
00:33:41.019 --> 00:33:44.022
Walsh. The dentist's bag.
it's empty. The money's gone.

642
00:33:44.090 --> 00:33:45.191
Where is it?

643
00:33:45.724 --> 00:33:46.725
Where is it?

644
00:34:41.280 --> 00:34:42.648
Am I crazy?

645
00:34:49.421 --> 00:34:51.056
We know you work
for the dentist.

646
00:34:51.123 --> 00:34:52.434
We're not mad. We
just want to get

647
00:34:52.458 --> 00:34:53.959
- the evidence back.
- Mmm-hmm.

648
00:34:54.025 --> 00:34:55.761
I don't know what
you're talking about.

649
00:34:55.827 --> 00:34:57.463
Only
one of you morons

650
00:34:57.529 --> 00:34:59.765
is going to get a deal
here. you understand?

651
00:34:59.831 --> 00:35:03.001
Now. right now your partner's
next door talking to my boss.

652
00:35:03.068 --> 00:35:06.172
Let's not forget. Foster is
a cop. He knows how it works.

653
00:35:06.238 --> 00:35:09.208
You think he's gonna keep his
mouth shut and go to jail?

654
00:35:09.275 --> 00:35:11.143
He's probably selling
you out right now.

655
00:35:11.210 --> 00:35:14.012
Think about it.

656
00:35:14.079 --> 00:35:16.014
You picked the wrong
precinct to rob. Benjamin.

657
00:35:16.081 --> 00:35:18.450
Oh. come on.
please. I did my homework.

658
00:35:18.517 --> 00:35:19.951
This place is a joke.

659
00:35:20.018 --> 00:35:22.254
Chaotic. disorganized.

660
00:35:22.321 --> 00:35:24.990
Too much personality.
not enough discipline.

661
00:35:25.056 --> 00:35:28.160
You give me 24 hours. I bet
you I could rob it again.

662
00:35:30.596 --> 00:35:32.440
You're gonna tell
me where that money is.

663
00:35:32.464 --> 00:35:34.032
Or what?

664
00:35:34.099 --> 00:35:36.302
What are you gonna do. Nancy?

665
00:35:36.802 --> 00:35:38.870
Hit me?

666
00:35:38.937 --> 00:35:41.139
Hey. Never mind.
Keebler's talking.

667
00:35:42.708 --> 00:35:44.810
Perfect.

668
00:35:44.876 --> 00:35:48.314
Enjoy your life at
Sing Sing. Benjy.

669
00:35:48.380 --> 00:35:50.916
Do you really think that
junior varsity psych crap

670
00:35:50.982 --> 00:35:52.951
is gonna work on me?

671
00:35:53.018 --> 00:35:55.954
I know that Bo is not
talking. and he knows I won't.

672
00:35:56.021 --> 00:35:57.489
So you got nothing.

673
00:36:27.419 --> 00:36:28.520
You had a bad dream.

674
00:36:31.623 --> 00:36:33.259
Maybe I am crazy.

675
00:37:08.026 --> 00:37:09.261
Help!

676
00:37:10.996 --> 00:37:12.197
Help!

677
00:37:13.365 --> 00:37:14.433
Leo! Hold on. buddy!

678
00:37:16.568 --> 00:37:17.603
Just hold on!

679
00:37:28.747 --> 00:37:29.781
Stand clear!

680
00:37:31.750 --> 00:37:33.552
Son of a bitch!

681
00:37:35.921 --> 00:37:38.757
Leo! Leo!

682
00:37:42.994 --> 00:37:44.162
Pal?

683
00:37:50.068 --> 00:37:51.136
Hey.

684
00:37:52.137 --> 00:37:53.672
Hey.

685
00:38:01.279 --> 00:38:03.081
He popped the couch.

686
00:38:04.316 --> 00:38:06.552
Told you
I wasn't crazy.

687
00:38:16.962 --> 00:38:18.029
Brand new day.

688
00:38:25.604 --> 00:38:26.805
Okay.

689
00:38:28.306 --> 00:38:31.410
I'm gonna call Nicole
and Captain Morgan.

690
00:38:35.681 --> 00:38:38.083
I'll take all the
heat. Thanks. you guys.

691
00:38:38.149 --> 00:38:40.852
-All righty. Here goes.
-Wait.

692
00:38:40.919 --> 00:38:45.757
Keebler's girlfriend said that he and
Foster rolled up to her place around 11:30.

693
00:38:45.824 --> 00:38:49.428
I'm thinking that they went
straight there from the precinct.

694
00:38:49.495 --> 00:38:51.497
They didn't have time to
drop the money anywhere.

695
00:38:51.563 --> 00:38:55.401
Right. The girlfriend said our
suspects stayed at her place

696
00:38:55.467 --> 00:38:57.235
until we came and arrested them.

697
00:38:57.302 --> 00:38:58.746
And we searched their
apartment. the van. Nothing.

698
00:38:58.770 --> 00:39:00.906
So. either they threw the
money out the window...

699
00:39:02.374 --> 00:39:03.942
Or they never had it
in the first place.

700
00:39:04.009 --> 00:39:07.913
The surveillance cameras did lose
Keebler and Foster for four minutes.

701
00:39:07.979 --> 00:39:10.458
Yeah. but if they didn't take it out
with them. what did they do with it?

702
00:39:10.482 --> 00:39:13.351
Nicole just paged us to
court. What do I tell her?

703
00:39:15.721 --> 00:39:17.355
Stall her.

704
00:39:17.423 --> 00:39:19.324
Look. if we can't
find this money.

705
00:39:19.391 --> 00:39:21.793
we've got to tell
the DA's office now.

706
00:39:23.094 --> 00:39:25.531
Detective Beaumont. listen
to me very carefully.

707
00:39:25.597 --> 00:39:29.100
This is my decision. I'm in
charge. Now. go stall my wife.

708
00:39:32.904 --> 00:39:35.073
She's right. Eddie. You
should call your wife.

709
00:39:50.822 --> 00:39:52.491
- The box.
- What?

710
00:39:52.558 --> 00:39:54.268
Somebody sent Sergeant
Brown a box yesterday.

711
00:39:54.292 --> 00:39:56.662
and it was full of these dolls.

712
00:39:56.728 --> 00:39:59.465
I put it on
that table right over there.

713
00:39:59.531 --> 00:40:01.500
- So?
- So. where's the box?

714
00:40:01.567 --> 00:40:04.069
Brown asked me to return
the box. and it's gone.

715
00:40:04.670 --> 00:40:05.871
Again. so?

716
00:40:05.937 --> 00:40:08.840
So Keebler and Foster knew
that they might get caught.

717
00:40:08.907 --> 00:40:11.209
But they had to make sure
that the money disappeared.

718
00:40:11.276 --> 00:40:14.513
They couldn't risk taking
it out in a backpack.

719
00:40:20.552 --> 00:40:22.120
Hey!

720
00:40:22.187 --> 00:40:23.655
I'm looking for a
box about that big.

721
00:40:23.722 --> 00:40:25.266
It would have been
dropped off last night.

722
00:40:25.290 --> 00:40:27.358
Last night's mail just went out.

723
00:40:27.425 --> 00:40:29.495
- so you can...
- Come on.

724
00:40:29.561 --> 00:40:31.329
Move. move. move! Move!

725
00:40:45.811 --> 00:40:48.146
Hey! Hey!

726
00:40:51.850 --> 00:40:53.585
Stop!

727
00:40:53.652 --> 00:40:54.772
What the hell are you doing?

728
00:40:54.820 --> 00:40:56.988
NYPD. Open the back.

729
00:41:17.743 --> 00:41:18.877
It'll be there.

730
00:41:20.546 --> 00:41:23.615
It's still sealed. Booking
slip intact. Now. move.

731
00:41:23.682 --> 00:41:25.793
Sirens all the way. Drive on
the sidewalk if you have to.

732
00:41:25.817 --> 00:41:26.885
Got it.

733
00:41:30.388 --> 00:41:32.090
- Good work. boss.
- Thank you.

734
00:41:32.157 --> 00:41:35.126
- Alvarez!
- Uh. Sarge. Yes.

735
00:41:35.193 --> 00:41:36.528
Status report.

736
00:41:38.463 --> 00:41:40.465
Uh. all is quiet. sir.

737
00:41:40.532 --> 00:41:43.268
We had a bomb threat last
night around 9:00 pm.

738
00:41:43.334 --> 00:41:45.203
but that turned
out to be a prank.

739
00:41:45.270 --> 00:41:47.138
Everything's normal.

740
00:41:47.606 --> 00:41:48.707
Is he lying?

741
00:41:48.774 --> 00:41:50.542
- No. sir.
- No. sir.

742
00:41:50.609 --> 00:41:52.210
Okay. what about
the banks thing?

743
00:41:52.277 --> 00:41:54.479
- The what?
- The Noho Strangler?

744
00:41:54.546 --> 00:41:56.181
Banks and Delahoy
just caught the guy.

745
00:41:56.247 --> 00:41:57.983
Haven't you been
following the radio calls?

746
